high and con\ntinue to advance.\n\u2014\u2014--o*()-\u2014\nEighteen battleships, including the\nnewly completed Wisconsin and Ne\nbraska, will leave San Francisco July\n6. Their ports of call, with the dis\ntances between in nautical miles, will\nhe, successively, Honolulu. Hawaii,\n2,100 miles; Pago-Pago, Samoa, 2,203\nmiles; .Melbourne, Australia, 575\nmiles; Manila, 3.772 miles; Colombo\nCeylon, 2,946 miles; Aden, Arabia, 2,\n130 miles; Suez, Egypt, 1.310 miles;\nPort Said, Egypt, 87 miles; Gibraltar,\n1,$20 miles; Hampton Roads. Virginia.\n3,207 miles. The total distance, exclu\nsive of possible variations that may be\nlater determined upon, will thus be\n23,204 miles from San Francisco, and\n36.96S miles in the entire world-cir\ncling voyage.\n\u20140*8*0\nCROP MOVING SEASON.\nThe \u201ccrop moving season\u201d this year\nis being prepared for by banks all\niver the country with more care than\never; for, after the recent storm, it is\nthe crucial point to be safely passed\nto insure the return of prosperity.\nLoans are being made with this in\nview, for the crops have become so\nbig that the last half of each year re\nquires half a billion dollars more cash\nto \u201cmove\u201d them than the first half\nyear requires. The \u201cmoving of the\nerop\u201d means transfer of ownership, by\nwhich the farmers\u2019 pay gets into gen\neral circulation.\n-o*o\nThe Memphis News Scimitar makes\nthe following terse argument in favor\nof a postal savings bank; \u201cThe Unit\ned States is about the only civilized\ncountry that has not a postal savings\nbank, and it will pick up this stitch\ndropped In its strenuous making of\nthe great fabric of an ideal republic\nby orderly evolution. A postal sav\nings bank encourages savings because\nit lias the confidence of all the people\nand prevents boarding from the same\nreason.\"\nCambridge Wen\nFor Third Time\nLondon, April I\u2014The eight, oared\nvarsity race between Oxford and Cam\nbridge over the Thames course was j\nwon for a third consecutive time today\nby Cambridge. The time was 10 min-]\nutes and 10 seconds.\n\nEthel Roosevelt\nRuns an Engine\njllearst. News Special to the Graphic,\nj Atlanta. April 4.-\u2014Miss Ethel Roose\nvelt, on the way with her mother and\nparty from Montgomery, ran a train\nfrom Newman here, a distance of 60\nmiles in '\u00bbG minutes and arrived\nahead of time. Engineer Still, who\nallowed the President\u2019s daughter to\ntake his place, said* he could not have\nconducted the mogul better himself.\n_\nDenounced Teddy\nand Bringham\nIlearst Xews Special to the Graphic.\nNew York, April 4.\u2014Ten thousand\nunemployed gathered in the Grand\nCentral Palace this afternoon and\nheard speeches denouncing the police\nfor breaking up their meeting last\nSaturday. The hall was well guarded\nand no trouble resulted. President\nRoosevelt and Inspector Bingham\nwere denounced, but in mild language.\nDR. C. C. CLINE\nMAY LEAVE CITY!\nHits Been Tendered the Vice I\u2019resi\ntleney and hair of .Mathematics in\nMaddox's \\en College at Eurekii\nSprings Is Considering; tlie .Mat\nter.\n\nj Doctor C. Cline, pastor of thtf<\nChristian church, has been tendered\nthe position of vice president and\nteacher af mathematics in A. S- .Mad\ndox's new college, which will \\tke the\nplace of the Crescent Hotel at Eureka\nSprings. Ark. The new position is\none that carries with it a iarg snmry\nand many inducements have tv i-n of\nfered to Doctor Cline to accept\nDoctor Cline stated yesterday tl at\nhe had not definitely decided as to his\ncourse. He is consulting .vita mem\nbers of his church to first assure him\nself that the change, if made, wo d\nbe agreeable. Doctor Cline was fo>\nmerly associated with Mr. Maddox at\nMaddox Seminary in Little Kfor\n'four years, and made an env'a >ir. rep\nutation as tin instructor. He has been\npastor of the Christian chu li here\nfor two years and has more \u2019ban dou\nbled its membership. He is regarded\nas one of the most, popular ministers\nin the city and his departure would\nhe regretted generally by his congre\ngation and his many friends.\nAT THE 4 HRISTIAN 1111(4 II.\nj\nTin* pastor will present at the morn\ning hour the subject of Worship, Its\nHelps anti Hindrances, and at night a\ndefinition of \u201cthe reasonable service\"\ndemanded by God of each responsible\nbeing. At each service the choir will\ngive special music.\nBANK CLERKS\nHAVE BALL TEAM\n\nAt a meeting of the bank clerks in\nthe parlors of the Simmons National\nBank yesterday the Bank Clerks Base\nball team was organized with I.. F.\nUnit as captain and manager. The\nfollowing team was signed for the\ni approaching season:\nH. Strange, catcher.\nI F. Milner, pitcher,\nj Veo B- Alexander, first base.\nK. Reinberger. second base.\nJunius Jordan, shortstop.\nL. F. Hutt, third base.\nFay Senyard, right field.\nH. Bryan, left field.\nHardy Kilgore, center field.\nThe team is open for games from\nany of the amateur teams.\n\u2014The Theatorium. otherwise known\nas the \u201ccrowd getter,\u201d announces the\nnew bill next week, including Lester's\nFamous Barnyard Circus- This circus\nhas with it dogs, sheep, pigs and goats,\nall of which act. Besides this the\nTheatorium will show some of the\nfinest films next week ever seen out\nside of New York.\nJJBRET JOHNSON'S\nLARGE ESTITE\n_ I\nWill Be Settled and Held In\ntact For the Benefit of\nWidow and Heirs\u2014Val\nued at $50,000\nSON ADMINISTRATOR\nKshitv it ml Ms Affairs in tlx- Hands <>f\n.1 u<lu<\u2018 E- J. Korn in. Who Ro|\u00bbi*c\nsrnts (lie Heirs. and Hunt A Toney.\nHhn Represent the Widow.\nThe estate of Jarrett Johnson, one\nof the richest colored citizens in this\npart, of the state, will he held intact\nfor the benefit of the heirs and widow.\nThe widow, Sallie Johnson, is rpere\nisented by her attorneys, Hunt Ton\ney. The heirs and their interest will\nhe looked after by Judge E. J. Kenvin.\nJarrett Johnson, who was most foul\nly murdered some two weeks ago\nwhile returning from the station of\nVarner in Lincoln county, on his way\nto his plantation. He was hauling\ncorn to his place which he had recent\nly purchased in Pine Bluff. From all\ninformation that can be secured it\nseems that the murderer of Johnson\nwas lying in wait and when lie passed\nlie shot Johnson and shattered his arm\nand then shot him in the side and\nrode off unconcernedly. From that\nhour to this he litis not been arrested,\nbut is still a fugitive from justice.\nJarrett Johnson during his life time\nwas one of the most conservative,\npeaceful and energetic citizens Lincoln\ncounty possessed among its coloretj\npopulation. He was a good business\nman and by bis quiet demeanor and\nstrict attendance to business amass\\l\na large fortune in the way of real pro\nperty and personal. Just a couple of\ndays before he was killed his case\nagainst the estate of Wiley Jones, de\nceased, was to have been heard in the\ncircuit court of Jefferson county. His\nclaim consisted of a note signed by Wi\nley Jones for $6,000 cash money bor\nrowed. Attorneys W. F. Coleman and\nIE. J- Kenvin represented Johnson in\nI this claim. The claim will be pressed\nfor the benefit of his widow and three\nheirs and placed to the credit of the\nestate. His administrator, who is one\nof his sons, will continue the suit in\ntic circuit court of this county. Jar\nrell Johnson kept his credit first class\nj and died leaving but few debts 1111\nj paid. These, under the administra\ntion, will he attended to as provided\nby the law of administration. He\nleaves as heirs to his large estate his\nwidow, Sallie Johnson; Jarrett John\nson Jr. and William Henry Johnson,\nhis two sons, and one daughter, now\nl living in Mississippi.\nThe estate is said to he worth $10,\nj 000.\nAttorneys E. J. Kenvin and H. K.\nI Toney leave Monday for Lincoln coun\ntv. where the matters necessary to he\ncomplied with under the law will be\ngiven immediate attention,\ni Johnson's plantation is one of the\nI best in this section of the state. Un\nder tin1 administration, crop will be\nmade for the present year and for\ni the benefit of the estate.\nLetters of administration have been\ngranted to William Henry Johnson by\nthe probate court of Lincoln county\nland the bond made b> the administra\ntor is said to lie one of the best of any\nfiled there in many years.\nTHREE NEGRO\n\u201cPREACHERS\u201d JAILED\ni Three barefooted, strong and able\nbodied negro preachers were taken in\nby the police last night, when they per\nsisted in holding a so-called religious\nmeeting at Fourth avenue and Main\nstreet. The men attracted many ne\ngroes to that corner and for a while\nthe streets around were blocked. They\nwere warned not to hold the meeting,\nI but did not heed the notice. The ne\nI groes arrived in the city yesterday\ni from a nearby point. They sang\npsalms all the way to the police sta\ntion and kept the prisoners in the jail\nawake for several hours afterwards,\nuntil they were threatened by them\nland their singing ceased. The negroes\nrefused to give their names and acted\nlike insane persons.\n__\nCroker is for\nW. J. Bryan\nHearst News Special to the Graphic.\nDublin, April t.\u2014.Richard Croker in\nan interview today declared that he\nwould come to America before the\nnext election and support Bryan.\nPicturesque Hats For Easter Wear\nIf yon liavt'ii i bought your\nKaster liar yet. conic down\n10 our .Millinery Parlors to\nniorrow and ehoosc from\nthose exquisite conceits .n\n(lower and ribbon trimmed\nCage Hats that we are sit\ning. Although lOaster s -o\nnear, our showing ol dainty\nDress Hats conrains hun\ndreds of pid ures(|iie crea\ntions. Tile prices tire so >vV\nfhat you can't resist them.\nHONNET COMPANY\nThe Home of Low Prices\n123 West Second Ave. P*ne Ark\n\nSOME STORES\nMake moreclaims than we do. \u201cSpecial\nSales,\u201d \u201cat less than cost,\u201d etc., etc,, but\nwhen you investigate and compare with\nour stock you will find you can get more\nfor